    "description": "Lilavati Hospital International Enterprises has an exciting opening for a Radiologist at our Gurgaon office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Lilavati Hospital International Enterprises:\nLilavati Hospital International Enterprises is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Flexible working hours\n• Learning & development budget\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gurgaon, Haryana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Lilavati Hospital International Enterprises!",
